  "texts": [
    "Wang et al.",
    "proposed BadAgent [272] by inserting the poisoned data into the trustworthy data during fine-tuning LLM for an LLM agent [290] for any specific task.",
    "proposed a new approach named Black-box Generative Model-based Attack (BGMAttack) to attack black-box generative models [133].",
    "Attack leverages text-generative models as non-robustness [133] triggers for executing backdoor attacks on classification without requiring explicit triggers like syntax.",
    "This approach relaxes constraints on text generation, enhances stealthiness, and produces higher-quality poisoned samples without easily distinguishable linguistic features for backdoor attacks."
  ],
